added.title: A Light Delivery
added.description: When Thomas accidentally breaks a light he's hauling to the Sodor Festival of Lights, he learns the best way to be the #1 engine is to be honest when you make a mistake.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: The Paint Problem
added.description: Thomas needs repainting and must be patient as he dries, even though he feels like he's missing out.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Caillou's Cricket/Dog Dilemma/The Spider Issue
added.description: Caillou inadvertently brings a cricket in the house./When Sarah gets a new dog, Caillou is actually a little jealous./Caillou feels afraid of real spiders.

added.title: Caillou Roller Skates/Say Lettuce!/Caillou Tries to Whistle
added.description: Caillou wants to learn how to roller skate./Caillou wants to take a picture of a bunny rabbit in Grandma's garden./ Clementine can whistle, and Caillou can't!

added.title: What's Ringette?/Rainy Day at the Beach/Caillou Climbs
added.description: Caillou and Leo want to play hockey./Caillou and his family are supposed to be enjoying a nice day./Mommy takes Caillou and Clementine to an indoor rock climbing wall.

added.title: Caillou the Patient/Caillou the Police Officer/Grandpa's Friend
added.description: While pretending to be a jet pilot Caillou falls down and scrapes his knees./When the traffic lights near school stop working a policeman comes to direct traffic./Grandpa takes Caillou to the park one fine day to meet his friend George.

added.title: A Sweet and Sour Day/Caillou's Puppet Show/Caillou's Collection
added.description: Caillou is helping Grandma water her flowers and fill the birdbath./Caillou and his friends Jason and Jeffrey make finger puppets at playschool and decide to put on a puppet show./In the park Caillou starts a new hobby - collecting rocks!

added.title: Hippoty Hoppity Voosh
added.description: Voooooosh! Bing and Sula are vooshing Hoppity and Fairy Hippo up higher and higher. What will happen when Fairy Hippo flies up a little too high and doesn't come back down again?

added.title: Dragon Breath
added.description: Bing and Pando are blowing steamy dragon breath outside when they find an icicle that makes Bing's hands icy cold! So they go inside for some hot chocolate. What happens when Bing doesn't wait for the hot chocolate to cool down?

added.title: Come On Charlie
added.description: Charlie is coming! And Bing has planned lots of games to play with him. But what happens when Charlie doesn't want to play any of the games Bing has put out?

added.title: Pocoyo's Balloon
added.description: Pocoyo is taking a walk with his beloved balloon when he is momentarily distracted by Loula and accidentally lets go of the balloon. He is flabbergasted as it drifts away up into the sky, and irreconcilably down in the dumps. Until we help him to realize that some things are more lasting than balloons: friends!

added.title: Who's' calling Me Now?
added.description: Pocoyo finds a box of unusual whistles. To his delight he discovers that each whistle makes a different noise and summons a different one of his chums. Fun until the tables are turned on Pocoyo and there's a whistle that summons him too. Everyone realizes how silly they're being.

added.title: Big Scary Slide
added.description: There's lots of new exciting playground rides in Pocoyoland including one huge daring slide. Pocoyo is too scared to give it a go. Pocoyo bravely helps his friend and overcomes his fear.

added.title: Elly's Shoes
added.description: Elly gets a fancy new pair of dressing up shoes. She loves wearing them so much that she won't take them off, even to go to bed!

added.title: Duck Stuck
added.description: Pocoyo finds a strange door. When he opens it, it seems to lead to the sky. Every time Pocoyo opens the door it seems to open up somewhere new.

added.title: Looking After Flop
added.description: Flop is sick and Bing explains that he wants to take care of him. So Bing tells Flop to sit on the sofa and gives him a pillow and a blanket, and Hoppity Voosh too! But making honey lemon is tricky hard.

added.title: Music
added.description: Bing, Sula and Pando are making music with Flop and Amma. Everyone has their own instruments, but they all want the drum. Pando gets to go first, but what will happen when it's time to swap and Sula gets the drum next?

added.title: Spinning Webs
added.description: Lucas questions his spider-hood when he can't spin a web properly.

added.title: I'm Taking You In
added.description: When Arlo's mom is out, Lucas looks after him. How hard can it be?

added.title: Water, Water Everywhere
added.description: Grumpy doesn't believe Funshine's warning that an invisible "Big Blob in the sky" is stealing water from a Whiffle garden -- he has pulled too many practical jokes before. To save the garden and his own credibility, Funshine must discover the truth of the menacing "Big Blob."

added.title: The Ultimate Bad Seed
added.description: Malcom becomes the new boss of Blusterland when he tricks Bluster into letting him transfer his inner-badness into a Bad Seed, leaving Bluster a polite shell of his former self. To neutralize the dangerous Seed before Malcom can use it to turn the Silver Lining into a giant Blusterland, the Care Bears must transfer its bad energy back into the only thing that can hold it, Bluster himself!

added.title: Who Said That?
added.description: Daffy learns a bad word and must learn not to use it.

added.title: The Magic of Spring
added.description: Bugs' failure as a magician turns to success when he experiences the true magic of nature.

added.title: New Cat in Town
added.description: Sylvester is jealous of the attention baby Pepe is receiving.

added.title: For Whom the Toll Calls
added.description: Petunia and Tweety learn how to call long distance and amass a huge phone bill.

added.title: Cereal Boxing
added.description: The kids become obsessed with getting the prizes from boxes of sugary cereal.

added.title: The Art of Friendship
added.description: When Chanterelle sees how good Lilit is at painting, she offers to help her dig into her talent. But Lilit's art lessons conflict with the fun project she has been working on with Mush-Mush and Chep. And when she sees that her friends are having a great time without her, Lilit is seriously annoyed which her paintings start showing.

added.title: The Rollinator
added.description: Chep is so good at moss-marbles, no one wants to play him anymore! No one except Sumush who reveals himself to be a tough competitor. To Chep's disbelief, Sumush keeps on winning. But Lilit and Mush-Mush convince their friend not to give up. Chep decides to play his favourite moss-marble: the Rollinator. The one marble he never risked playing before.

removed.title: To Catch a Fly
removed.description: When Findley watches a show about spiders eating flies, he thinks Lucas wants to eat him!

removed.title: Picture This!
removed.description: The babies create their own endings to fairytales.

removed.title: A Clean Sweep
removed.description: Daffy tries to avoid cleaning up by sweeping his toys under a rug.

removed.title: The Super-Long Shortcut
removed.description: When Gordon is unable to make an important delivery on his own, Thomas offers his help, but Gordon insists on second-guessing Thomas's every move.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Captain Caillou/The Loudest Noise/Caillou's First Wedding
removed.description: Grandpa's got a surprise for Caillou on their trip to the park - it's a remote control sailboat!/Mommy sends Caillou to play outside because he's making too much noise and it's Rosie's nap time./Daddy and Mommy's friend Jonas is getting married.

removed.title: Daffy Did It!
removed.description: Tweety blames Daffy for his mistake, and then has trouble living with the guilt of lying.

removed.title: The Mysterious Seepod
removed.description: Chep has come across a new seedpod specimen. Mushpot warns him not to take it though. But the temptation is too much and Chep can't resist taking the seedpod and opening it to find it is full of itchy powder! Argh! Mush-Mush and Lilit do their best to help their friend, but it seems like the only way Chep can get rid of the itching is to ask Mushpot for a remedy.

removed.title: Power Outage
removed.description: The Care Bears come to the aid of a group of Whiffles whose worries are blanketing their garden with such bad vibes that plants won't grow. When the Care Bear Stare isn't powerful enough to help, Grumpy comes to the rescue with the invention of a robotic Care Bear Stare amplifier.

removed.title: A Present for Mommy/Caillou the Chef/Caillou the Painter
removed.description: Mommy's having a bad day - first she can't find her car keys, then she and Caillou have to shovel the car out, and then the car won't start!/Jeffrey and Jason are coming over for dinner - it's a make-your-own pizza party!/Caillou's got a brand new painting shirt and decides to paint something for Grandma.

removed.title: Hair Cut-Ups
removed.description: Lola is afraid of getting her first haircut.

removed.title: The Disappearing Mushler
removed.description: Mush-Mush can't wait to show his tricks of forest illusion to everyone. But Amanita keeps ruining Mush-Mush's performance by figuring out all his tricks. Grrr! When Mush-Mush decides to do his famous 'Disappearing Mushable' trick on Truff, Truff really disappears! And now, Amanita and Mush-Mush must join forces to find their disappearing friend.

removed.title: Sliding
removed.description: Lucas and Findley find an ice cube. When Lucas rides the ice cube in the sink and falls down the drain, a scared Findley rallies to save him.

removed.title: Caillou the Librarian/Caillou the Bookworm/Caillou the Storyteller
removed.description: Caillou is excited about showing Rosie the ropes when they visit the library./Returning home from the library Caillou is very eager to sit down and enjoy his pirate book./It's a rainy day at playschool and the children can't go outside.

removed.title: Where Oh Where Has Our Funshine Gone?
removed.description: When Funshine uses the Care Bears' work time to develop his latest comic book character, his creative playtime jeopardizes the success of the team's mission to a strange part of the Silver Lining.

removed.title: Caillou's Surprise/A Surprise for Miss Martin/A Surprise Sleepover
removed.description: When Caillou accidentally breaks Mommy's favorite cup, Grandma suggests they make her a new one./When Caillou finds out that Miss Martin's birthday is coming up, he wants to do something very special for her./Sarah is playing at Caillou's house when a sudden rainstorm causes a power outage.

removed.title: Tyrannosaurus Wrecks
removed.description: Thomas and the other Engines get to deliver some newly discovered dinosaur bones, but they must deliver them in the correct order for assembly, which isn't as easy as it sounds...
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: New on the Planet
removed.description: Pocoyo is scared when a stranger appears in Pocoyoland, but he soon comes to realize that he needn't be scared of this little alien and they become friends.

removed.title: Shoo, Shoo Bird, Fly Away!/Caillou's Road Trip/Caillou and the Dragon
removed.description: When birds keep eating the seeds in Mommy and Caillou's newly planted garden, they come up with the idea of making a scarecrow./One fine day the family is going on a car trip./There's a special visitor at Caillou's playschool - a boy named Alan who has Down Syndrome.

removed.title: Pig Who Cried Woof
removed.description: Petunia fakes emergencies. But when a real one arises, no one believes her.

removed.title: Elly's Ballet Class
removed.description: Elly wants to be a prima ballerina with a troupe of other dancers so she tries to teach her friends to dance just like her. But she gets frustrated that they can't do it straight away and is very bossy. Finally everyone dances together in their own special way.

removed.title: Mural
removed.description: Sula and Amma are painting a mural when Bing and Flop arrive and help. Amma reminds Bing that when painting, it's important to remember to "Dip it... and... Wipe it" to stop the drips! But what will happen when Bing forgets to wipe his brush?

removed.title: Acorns
removed.description: Bing and Sula are collecting and counting acorns in the Howly Woods. But when they start to disappear, Flop explains that they need to stay mousy quiet to find out where they're going!

removed.title: Mad Mix Machine
removed.description: Pocoyo finds a super duper machine that mixes objects and makes special new toys to play with. But when Pocoyo puts his friends' toys in the machine for fun, he upsets them. Eventually Pocoyo has to put things back to normal and then share his new magic machine with his friends so they can all enjoy it.

removed.title: The Messy Guest
removed.description: Pocoyo is having a lovely time playing with his friends but little does he realize that he's making a mess and leaving them to clear it all up! When he sees that his friends no longer want to play with him, he comes to understand the importance not only of having fun and making a mess, but of helping and clearing up too.

removed.title: Pocoyo's Present
removed.description: Pocoyo has a beautifully wrapped up present but he won't open it. Elly is dying to know what's inside. She begs and pleads but when that fails she turns to desperate measures.

removed.title: Hiding
removed.description: Bing is helping Flop in Padget's shop when he decides to hide from Flop! But what will happen when Bing hides in Padget's store room and gets locked in?

removed.title: Sandcastle
removed.description: Bing and Flop are building sandcastles when Pando comes to help with Don the Dumpertruck! But what will happen when Pando realizes Don's starter key is being used as a decoration on Bing's sandcastle?

removed.title: Jingly Shoes
removed.description: Charlie really wants to try to walk and with the help of Bing's jingly shoes he takes his first steps! But what will happen when Coco suggests Charlie should keep them?
